cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the verification of higher-order programs using behavioral software contracts. It discusses the use of abstract reduction semantics to handle missing or opaque components of a program, which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of automated reasoning tools for contract verification, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE) and formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses the soundness and computability of the proposed approach, which falls under cryptography and security (cs.CR).
